ignore_warnings.description: If true, allow backwards incompatible changes.

instance.description: The name of the instance to create the schema bundle within.

name.description: The unique name of the requested schema bundle. Values are of the form 'projects/<project>/instances/<instance>/tables/<table>/schemaBundles/<schemaBundleId>'.

schema_bundle_id.description: The unique name of the schema bundle in the form '[_a-zA-Z0-9][-_.a-zA-Z0-9]*'.

table.description: The name of the table to create the schema bundle within.

proto_descriptors.description: Base64 encoded content of the file.

block.description: File descriptor set, generated by protoc. To generate, use protoc with imports and source info included. For an example test.proto file, the following command would put the value in a new file named out.pb. $ protoc --include_imports --include_source_info test.proto -o out.pb
